sequenceDiagram
    participant User as Data Scientist
    participant Dashboard as ODH Dashboard
    participant KubeAuth as kube-auth-proxy
    participant Kubeflow as Kubeflow Controller
    participant Notebook as Notebook Pod
    participant S3 as S3 Storage
    participant Pipelines as DS Pipelines
    participant Argo as Argo Workflows
    participant ModelReg as Model Registry
    participant MLMeta as ml-metadata
    participant KServe as KServe Controller
    participant Gateway as Envoy Gateway
    participant EPP as llm-d-inference-scheduler
    participant vLLM as vLLM Pod
    participant GuardGW as vllm-orchestrator-gw
    participant GuardOrch as fms-guardrails-orch
    participant Detectors as guardrails-detectors
    participant Client as External Client

    Note over User,Client: ═══ Workflow 1: Model Serving via KServe ═══

    User->>Gateway: POST InferenceService CR
    Gateway->>KubeAuth: ext_authz check
    KubeAuth-->>Gateway: Authenticated (OAuth2/OIDC)
    Gateway->>Dashboard: Forward to API
    Dashboard->>KServe: Create InferenceService CR
    KServe->>KServe: Reconcile: create Deployment,<br/>Service, HTTPRoute
    KServe->>Gateway: Configure HTTPRoute
    Note over KServe: storage-initializer init container
    KServe->>S3: Download model artifacts<br/>(HTTPS/443, IAM creds)
    KServe->>vLLM: Start predictor pod
    Note over vLLM: Model loaded, ready for inference

    Client->>Gateway: POST /v1/chat/completions<br/>(HTTPS/443, TLS 1.2+)
    Gateway->>vLLM: Forward to InferenceService pod<br/>(HTTP/8000)
    vLLM->>vLLM: Run inference
    vLLM-->>Gateway: Prediction result
    Gateway-->>Client: JSON response (HTTPS)

    Note over User,Client: ═══ Workflow 2: LLM Inference with llm-d Scheduling ═══

    Client->>Gateway: POST /v1/chat/completions<br/>(HTTPS/443)
    Gateway->>EPP: ext_proc gRPC filter<br/>(9002/TCP)
    EPP->>EPP: Score pods by KV-cache hit,<br/>queue depth, load
    EPP-->>Gateway: Selected target pod IP
    Gateway->>vLLM: Route to selected prefill worker<br/>(HTTP/8000)
    vLLM->>vLLM: Process prefill phase
    Note over vLLM: Transfer KV-cache to decode worker
    vLLM-->>Gateway: Streaming tokens
    Gateway-->>Client: SSE streaming response

    Note over User,Client: ═══ Workflow 3: Notebook Development ═══

    User->>Gateway: Access Dashboard<br/>(HTTPS/443)
    Gateway->>KubeAuth: ext_authz check
    KubeAuth->>KubeAuth: OAuth2/OIDC flow<br/>(→ OpenShift OAuth server)
    KubeAuth-->>Gateway: Authenticated
    Gateway->>Dashboard: Forward to UI
    User->>Dashboard: Create notebook workbench
    Dashboard->>Kubeflow: Create Notebook CR
    Kubeflow->>Kubeflow: Reconcile: create StatefulSet,<br/>Service, HTTPRoute
    Note over Kubeflow: odh-notebook-controller injects<br/>kube-rbac-proxy sidecar + NetworkPolicy
    Kubeflow->>Notebook: Launch notebook pod

    User->>Gateway: Access notebook<br/>(HTTPS/443, per-notebook HTTPRoute)
    Gateway->>KubeAuth: ext_authz check
    KubeAuth-->>Gateway: Authenticated
    Gateway->>Notebook: Forward to Jupyter<br/>(via kube-rbac-proxy sidecar)
    Notebook->>S3: Download training data<br/>(HTTPS/443)
    Note over Notebook: Train model in notebook
    Notebook->>S3: Upload model artifacts

    Note over User,Client: ═══ Workflow 4: Pipeline-Driven Model Registration ═══

    User->>Dashboard: Submit pipeline run
    Dashboard->>Pipelines: Create PipelineRun
    Pipelines->>Argo: Create Workflow DAG
    Argo->>Argo: Execute pipeline steps
    Argo->>S3: Store pipeline artifacts<br/>(HTTPS/443)
    Argo->>ModelReg: Register model<br/>(REST/8080, Istio mTLS)
    ModelReg->>MLMeta: Store metadata<br/>(gRPC/8080)
    ModelReg->>S3: Record artifact location
    Argo->>KServe: Create InferenceService CR<br/>(auto-deploy step)
    KServe->>S3: Download model
    KServe->>vLLM: Deploy model endpoint

    User->>Dashboard: View model in registry
    Dashboard->>ModelReg: Fetch model metadata<br/>(BFF/8043, TLS 1.3)
    ModelReg-->>Dashboard: Model info + serving status
    Dashboard-->>User: Display model card + endpoint URL

    Note over User,Client: ═══ Workflow 5: Guardrailed Inference ═══

    Client->>GuardGW: POST /v1/chat/completions<br/>(HTTP/8090)
    GuardGW->>GuardOrch: Forward request<br/>(HTTP/8033)
    GuardOrch->>Detectors: Run input detectors<br/>(HTTP/8080, NetworkPolicy only)
    Detectors-->>GuardOrch: Detection results<br/>(PII, toxicity, etc.)

    alt Input blocked
        GuardOrch-->>GuardGW: 400 blocked response
        GuardGW-->>Client: Blocked: policy violation
    else Input passes
        GuardOrch->>vLLM: Forward to LLM<br/>(HTTP/8000)
        vLLM-->>GuardOrch: LLM response
        GuardOrch->>Detectors: Run output detectors
        Detectors-->>GuardOrch: Output detection results
        GuardOrch-->>GuardGW: Filtered response
        GuardGW-->>Client: Safe response
    end
